This paper deals with the problem of explaining the outcomes of machine learning models, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the ethical implications of using these explanations, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for searching for fair rule lists, which could be relevant to the field of emerging technologies (cs.ET).
